Title : Operation Ceasefire (guns-for-tickets program)
Text : '''Operation Ceasefire''' is the name for a guns-for-tickets exchange program that was run by the [[Denver, Colorado|Denver]] Police Department, in conjunction with the [[Denver Nuggets]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Nuggets' Ellis makes mark with little fanfare |author=Boeck, Greg |publisher=USA Today |date=October 14, 1993}}</ref> [[Colorado Rockies]], and [[Denver Broncos]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Bengals, Bucs protest ruling |date=December 16, 1993 |publisher=USA Today}}</ref> in the late 1990s.

